list.name: Default
list.comment: Changed BNB algorithm to check lower bound before adding node to processors - now it is much faster

task.summary: fixed loop so that scheduler passes tests
Fixed bug in OutputSchedule class to do with running on one processor.
Added a method to keep track of number of schedules checked as branches are pruned by future algorithms - to be used by future progress bar in visualisation.

First commit for BNB branch - changed certain methods using Strings to identify nodes to use Node objects instead. Added equals() method to Node to facilitate this. Added new class BNBAlgorithm that is currently a copy of DFS, with an added method to set Bottom Level Weights in each node. Nodes now have fields for children and bottom level weight. currently scheduler is working, but very incorrectly - unsure why but will focus on making working BNBAlgorithm on this branch.

Refactored heavily to allow for BNB implementation - many changes needed to be made mostly to NodeList (which is now called PartialSchedule). Node objects now exist for all PartialSchedules and do not store any schedule-specific information such as start time. This information is now stored by keys in PartialSchedule. Also changed the way edges are kept track of by implementing subclass IncomingEdge, though this may not have been necessary. Added calls to update schedule pruning count - still not reaching calculated upper bound on schedules - may need to discuss this and re-try.
